      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LONESTAR WARRIOR (7) produced a strong performance last time when he battled on bravely to just miss out over 1800m at this track. Interesting to see what unfolds from this wide draw. Meets a similar line up and he is a strong winning hope. DEE JAYS MISS (6) disappointed backers at the first run back from a break last start when fifth, beaten 13 metres over 1800m at this track when sent out as the favourite. Meets a similar line up and she is capable of a much better performance. PERFECT PLAYGIRL (5) was responsible for a better effort last time out when third over 1800m at this track. Should run a big race. JAPANESE MIKI (4) was out of the money two runs ago then broke and finished seventh last start over 1800m at this track, coming home 25 metres from the winner. This doesn't look as hard so he is capable of turning things around.",
